  annote = {
    O analiza a uneletelor folosite pentru testarea
    sistemelor IoT, motivata de faptul ca metodele
    de testare existente sunt insuficiente.
    Autorii sustin ca provocarile similare din alte domenii
    (software, cloud, etc) au fost adresate, dar in
    IoT inca nu. Asa ca isi propun sa identifice
    intrebari de cercetare si probleme in 
    testarea de sisteme IoT.
    
    Articolul contine o taxonomie foarte buna a tipurilor
    de testare pe care o pot folosi la mine in teza.
    Vorbeste si despre tipurile de test beds:
    fizice, simulate, emulate. Articolul propune o lista
    de provocari aduse de iot: heterogenitate,
    disteme distribuite, cloud si embdeded toate combinate.
    
    "Even further, we can consider that there is a gap on tools
    that can test distributed and heterogeneous systems, especially
    in an automated way, however there exists ongoing work on
    covering these lacks"
    
    "Some gaps appear in the solutions support 
    of different languages and platforms. 
    A vast part of the available tools focus 
    on a specific platform, language or 
    standard, lacking the support for 
    heterogeneity of the IoT field"
    
    "However, it is easily noticeable that 
    there is a lack of tools for testing 
    certain artifacts such as: security  
    and privacy, regulatory testing and 
    firmware/software upgrade  (e.g. out-of-the-box 
    continuous integration functionalities)."
